&lt;p&gt;The Staff Bank is seeking a qualified Consultant for flexible work in a hospital setting in Kingston. If you are experienced in OrthoGeriatrics and looking for flexible working hours in Kingston Hospital NHS Foundation Trust please apply today..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff Bank can offer you the flexibility you desire with the benefit of the NHS pension scheme, and more. Our jobs would bring a brilliant opportunity to anyone who is looking to top up their current salary, skills or to accommodate their personal circumstances. You’ll be reliable, dedicated and flexible, with a commitment to competent, high quality care delivery.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;StaffBank requires you to have: &lt;br /&gt;* Registration with the GMC&lt;br /&gt;* Eligibility to work within the UK &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;StaffBank can offer you: &lt;br /&gt;* Flexible hours&lt;br /&gt;* Free Mandatory training and annual updates&lt;br /&gt;* Support from a friendly and approachable team&lt;br /&gt;* Excellent, Competitive pay rates &lt;br /&gt;* Access to the NHS Pension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the recruitment process you will be required to provide or complete an enhanced DBS/CRB check. We regret that we cannot accept applications from candidates seeking work permits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to find out more about this incredible opportunity! Successful candidates will also have an opportunity to learn about our great benefits! Please apply directly to this advertisement by submitting your current CV, or for further information on the roles please contact the Kingston Hospital Staff Bank Team on 0333 577 3411&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details contact:&lt;br /&gt;Taylor Dowell- Senior Recruitment Consultant - ; Taylor.Dowell@bankpartners.co.uk&lt;/p&gt;
